                <td bgColor="#ECECEC"><textarea cols="48" name="Message" rows="12" wrap="VIRTUAL" onselect="storeCaret(this);" onclick="storeCaret(this);" onkeyup="storeCaret(this);" onchange="storeCaret(this);">[quote][i]Originally posted by Zerp[/i]
[br]As mentioned above, to run faster the easiest option is to buy sow potions. 
Something that was not mentioned is the use of DMF. If you are hunting over hilly areas, DMF can often help you gain distance from your target. You levitate, mobs walk up and down hill thus making their path longer. With a bit of inventiveness, it can be used in many spots to your advantage.
Items with extended range help as well. Often times, it will be hard to resnare a planar mob even if you can outrun it, cause it will cover your spell casting range faster than you can cast dooming darkness... Extended range makes is less of an issue (a Drachnid Thyxl, or however that is spelled, is very easy to get... and cermaic swords are getting cheaper by the day).
[/quote]</textarea><br /></td>
