                <td bgcolor="#ECECEC" valign="top"><font color="#000000" face="arial" size="2"><small>Posted&nbsp;-&nbsp;08/02/2003&nbsp;: 12:16:53 AM</small><hr size="2"><span class="spnMessageText"> I was not twinked, and I could solo a Hill giant at level 29 (mana intensively).  At level 34, you should be able to take them no problem.  I suggest you hunt in The Overthere as it is the best experience at that level unless you group in HighKeep.  Group in HighKeep or Solo in The Overthere until level 39 and then get those rangers/druids in West Commonlands.  You will make oodles of plat there (the vendor is on Beta Neutral faction, so never adds and not KOS) and some of the best experience.  Do them until 41 and then get the Skeletons in Dreadlands.  Pull with Darkness, Slow on incoming, sic pet and kite it around until pet gets agro.  Then put Boil Blood and Vampiric Curse on it to counter the Call of Bones and hit it with an undead nuke every now and then (very mana efficient spells).  Do that until 44.  You can also charm kite them (wayyy faster kills) but that's dangerous.  Your hasted pet may turn on you at the worst times.<br /><br />At level 44, go to the Spiroc in Timorous Deep and fear kite them (have to learn pathing and how they add and stuff, so keep FD up) until level 51.  At 51, you can go kill Seafuries in OOT, or nobles/bards in HK until around level 54ish.  I suggest you start looking for more groups at 51 Lol.  PoP has made all those other zones go empty :(  Oh, you can charm kite in The Grey really well at 51+.  Enduring Breath (i.e. DMF) required, though.<br /><br />Stop thinking about l3wtz and level up.  When you get to level 49, you pet will be able to solo a Hill Giant without your help.  Just make sure you have enough (and high enough research if you can manage) to get/research/buy all your spells as you ding.  You never know when you will need to Root-DoT (with all DoT lines like I did ROFL) for good exp.  It's bored as hell, but when you're getting 4% exp a kill, I can manage.</span></font></td>
